### What I did (and why it should stop the OOM crashes)
- **IDE OOM hardening is in place**: `node_modules/` + `.git/` + large artifact folders are excluded via **`.cursorignore`** and **`.vscode/settings.json`** (you also added `.git` exclusions), so Cursor shouldnt try to index/watch them.
- **Debug corpus stays out of the workspace**: `server.js` reads it via `DEBUG_CORPUS_DIR` (fallback to `debug/`), preventing the giant local corpuses from re-triggering indexing OOM.

If Cursor still OOMs after these changes, do **Developer: Reload Window** so Cursor re-applies ignore rules.

